# -------------------------------------
# Example of environment variable setup
# -------------------------------------

# 1. Google Sheets (Service Account JSON)

# To get the Google Sheets credentials (JSON file):

# A) Create a project in Google Cloud Console:
#    - Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
#    - Create a new project or select an existing one.

# B) Enable the required APIs:
#    - Enable **Google Sheets API** and **Google Drive API**:
#      - Go to "APIs & Services" → "Library" → search and enable:
#        - Google Sheets API
#        - Google Drive API

# C) Create a Service Account:
#    - Go to "IAM & Admin" → "Service Accounts".
#    - Create a new service account and download the **JSON file**.

# D) Grant access to your Google Sheets document:
#    - Open the Google Sheets document you want to use and share it with the email from the service account.
#    - The email will look like `your-service-account@your-project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com`.

# E) Save the JSON as an environment variable:
#    - **Do not upload the JSON file to GitHub**.
#    - In Windows (PowerShell), use:
#      setx GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_JSON "<PASTE_THE_JSON_CONTENT_HERE>"
#    - In Mac/Linux (Terminal), use:
#      export GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_JSON="<PASTE_THE_JSON_CONTENT_HERE>"
GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_JSON=PASTE_HERE_YOUR_JSON_CONTENT

# 2. YouTube Data API Key

# To get the YouTube Data API key:

# A) Go to Google Cloud Console:
#    - Visit https://console.cloud.google.com/
#    - Select the project you created earlier, or create a new one.

# B) Enable the **YouTube Data API**:
#    - Go to "APIs & Services" → "Library".
#    - Search and enable **YouTube Data API v3**.

# C) Create an **API Key**:
#    - Go to "APIs & Services" → "Credentials".
#    - Click "Create Credentials" and select **API Key**.

# D) Save the **API Key** as an environment variable:
#    - In Windows (PowerShell), use:
#      setx YT_API_KEY "<YOUR_YOUTUBE_API_KEY>"
#    - In Mac/Linux (Terminal), use:
#      export YT_API_KEY="<YOUR_YOUTUBE_API_KEY>"
YT_API_KEY=YOUR_YOUTUBE_API_KEY
